<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-15T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-15T02:00:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11/5–1551: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-15T16:00:00+09:00">May 15,
                                    1951—4 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3376. To Acheson for Under Secretary Matthews.<note n="1" xml:id="d87fn1">The telegram was circulated to Nolting, Nitze, and Merchant.</note>
                            Additional possibility makes it desirable for Marshall and Chase to
                            postpone departure until May 23.<note n="2" xml:id="d87fn2">Telegram
                                3850 to Hong Kong, May 18, 1951, informed Marshall and Chase that
                                their plan to remain in Hong Kong until May 23 was approved
                                (110.11/5–1851).</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>